## 1. Headline read

Outstanding print across the board — 11th consecutive quarter of double-digit revenue growth, with Cloud accelerating to +63% y/y, crossing $20B/quarter for the first time, and backlog nearly doubling sequentially to $462B. Revenue beat consensus by ~2.7%; reported EPS of $5.11 beat consensus by ~91% but was meaningfully flattered by $37.7B of "other income" (unrealized equity gains). The call confirms the AI-capable-incumbent thesis on every dimension that matters (capability, distribution, monetization) while also confirming the compute-constraint and capex-intensity reality. No prior GOOGL notes exist in `notes/GOOGL/`, so this is the first observation in our local record — trajectory anchoring relies on watchlist baseline scores only.

