## 3. Forward guidance

- **FY26 CapEx raised to $180–190B** from prior $175–185B, primarily to include Intersect acquisition closed in March. "Unprecedented internal and external demand for AI compute resources" (Ashkenazi, p.12).
- **2027 CapEx to "significantly increase compared to 2026"** — explicit forward signal of another step-function up (Ashkenazi, p.13). This is the single most material forward statement on the call.
- **Q2 FX tailwind ~1pp** to consolidated revenue, down from 3pp in Q1 (Ashkenazi, p.12).
- **TPU hardware sales to third parties** begin "later this year" (small contribution in 2026); "vast majority of revenues to be realized in 2027" (Ashkenazi, p.12). Lumpy quarter-to-quarter.
- **Cloud margin headwind from Wiz** — "low single-digit percentage point headwind to Cloud's operating margin for the remainder of 2026" (Ashkenazi, p.12).
- **Backlog conversion:** "just over half" of the $462B backlog converts to revenue in the next 24 months (Ashkenazi, p.11; reiterated p.20).
- **Dividend:** 5% increase to quarterly dividend (Ashkenazi, p.11).
- **Tone:** Pichai — "we are not slowing down" (summary, p.7); Ashkenazi — "outstanding" / "robust" used repeatedly. No sandbagging signals detected.
