## 8. Management Q&A flags

1. **TPU pricing philosophy dodge (Brian Nowak Q1, p.13–14).** Pichai gave a high-level "ROIC framework" answer but did NOT quantify how external TPU pricing compares to internal opportunity cost. The phrase "we step back and think about it overall as the opportunity for Google Cloud" telegraphs that TPU hardware sales pricing is designed to NOT cannibalize Cloud workloads where GOOGL captures more margin. Watch the TPU revenue mix disclosure in Q2/Q3 — if pricing comes in low, it signals deeper anxiety about NVDA's lock on the workload.
2. **Search ad-coverage ratio non-answer (Doug Anmuth Q2, p.14–15).** Anmuth asked specifically about increasing ad coverage above the historical "20%" Google has held to. Schindler said "I think there is upside in that coverage number" but didn't quantify. This is meaningful — if GOOGL is moving above 20% ad density in AI Mode / new surfaces, that's a margin lever no buyside model is fully pricing in. Worth pressuring on the next print.
3. **Sandbagging on Gemini App ad monetization (Michael Nathanson follow-up, p.16–17).** "We're not rushing anything here" while sitting on 350mm paid subs and an explicit acknowledgment that "ads have always been a big part of scaling products to reach billions of people" — classic optionality preservation. There is a material revenue rail being deliberately deferred. Bullish-deferred, not bearish.
4. **Wiz margin headwind admission (Ashkenazi prepared, p.12).** Low-single-digit pp Cloud margin headwind from Wiz for remainder of 2026. Acknowledged proactively — clean disclosure but worth tracking for whether actual drag overshoots.
5. **Supply chain inflation deflection (Ken Gawrelski Q1, p.19).** Pichai's answer on factoring supply chain inflation into CapEx was vague — "the scale at which we are operating and our ability to work across all layers" — i.e., we have leverage on suppliers, we're not pricing it in explicitly. If TSMC/HBM costs spike, the CapEx number is going up beyond $180–190B (and the ROIC narrative needs adjusting).

